{
  "texts": [
    "Similarly, we performed the same operations after extracting features from the MaxViT model.",
    "The results from both auxiliary classifiers are joined together to create a unified feature representation.",
    "The feature vector, which contains information from both the DenseNet-201 and MaxVit models, is then processed into a final classifier.",
    "The final classification block consists of a dropout layer, which helps prevent overfitting, a flattening operation, and a linear layer that translates the combined feature vector to the number of target classes.",
    "The ultimate result is achieved by using a LogSoftmax Figure 2layer, which provides that the output probabilities are standardized and appropriate for classification purposes."
  ]
}